==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: American Protective Association
<hw>A*mer"i*can Pro*tect"ive As*so`ci*a"tion</hw>. <def>A secret
organization in the United States, formed in Iowa in 1887, ostensibly
for the protection of American institutions by keeping Roman Catholics
out of public office. Abbrev. commonly to <abbr><it>A. P
.A</it></abbr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

